    ],
  ],
  higher: [
    [
      `At ${page.annualFormatted}, your salary is ${percentOfMedian}% of the UK median (${formatCurrency(medianAnnual)}). This places you well above the average earner. Your monthly take-home of ${page.englandFormatted.netMonthly} provides significant spending power in all UK regions.`,
      `The 30% housing rule gives a budget of ${rentBudget30} per month, which covers quality accommodation in most areas. Mortgage capacity at 4.5x salary is ${mortgageMax}, opening up a wide range of the UK property market.`,
      `At the higher rate, pension contributions become even more valuable. Every £100 contributed via salary sacrifice saves you £48 in combined tax and NI. If you are close to the higher rate threshold, increasing pension contributions can effectively reduce your marginal rate from 40% to 20%.`,
    ],
    [
      `Earning ${page.annualFormatted} per year puts you at ${percentOfMedian}% of the national median. With a net monthly income of ${page.englandFormatted.netMonthly}, you have the financial capacity for comfortable living, meaningful savings, and investment.`,
      `Your housing budget under the 30% guideline is ${rentBudget30} per month. Mortgage borrowing power at 4.5 times salary reaches ${mortgageMax}, which is competitive across most of the UK property market outside prime London postcodes.`,
