    ],
    [
      `A salary of ${page.annualFormatted} is well above the UK median. At ${percentOfMedian}% of the average, you take home ${page.englandFormatted.netMonthly} per month. Your effective rate of ${page.englandFormatted.effectiveTaxRate} reflects the progressive nature of the UK tax system.`,
      `Housing: ${rentBudget30}/month under the 30% rule; mortgage capacity of ${mortgageMax}. These figures support property ownership in most UK regions. For London, a dual-income household at this level can access much of the market.`,
      `At the higher rate, every pound of pension contribution saves 40p in tax plus 2p in NI above the upper earnings limit. This makes pension planning one of the most impactful financial decisions you can make at this salary level.`,
    ],
  ],
  taper: [
    [
      `At ${page.annualFormatted}, your salary is ${percentOfMedian}% of the UK median. However, the personal allowance taper between £100,000 and £125,140 means your marginal rate is effectively 60%. Your take-home of ${page.englandFormatted.netMonthly}/month reflects this higher burden.`,
      `Housing is well within reach: ${rentBudget30}/month at 30% of net, and mortgage capacity of ${mortgageMax}. At this income, the focus shifts from affording essentials to optimising tax efficiency.`,
      `The most powerful strategy in the taper zone is pension contributions. Every £100 contributed via salary sacrifice saves £60 in effective tax (due to the taper). If you can bring your adjusted net income below £100,000, you restore the full personal allowance of ${formatCurrency(PERSONAL_ALLOWANCE)}, saving up to £5,028 in additional tax.`,
    ],
    [
      `Earning ${page.annualFormatted} places you firmly in the personal allowance taper zone. At ${percentOfMedian}% of the UK median, your income is substantial but the 60% effective marginal rate significantly impacts each additional pound earned. Your personal allowance has been reduced to ${formatCurrency(page.england.personalAllowance)}.`,
      `Your monthly take-home of ${page.englandFormatted.netMonthly} supports a housing budget of ${rentBudget30} and mortgage capacity of ${mortgageMax}. Financial planning at this level should focus heavily on tax-efficient strategies.`,
